{"key":"post-9927868","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9927868</id>\n<content>NEVER use a 'frosting' layer.&amp;nbsp; Agar tried it and failed.&amp;nbsp; He made a post the first time it worked, but later realized like all of us do that it was a bad idea.&amp;nbsp; Never leave grains exposed on the surface.&amp;nbsp; They dry out and the mycelium stops growing, leaving the grain available to germinate trichoderma spores as soon as you mist the top, thus hydrating the grains/contaminants.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>9927771</prev>\n<first>9921161</first>\n<last>9927868</last>\n<when>1236451417</when>\n<utime>03/07/09 08:43 PM</utime>\n</post>"}